@olivierGATSNCF tried this with buildah 1.3 and it works fine for me. After you create your image with buildah installed in it, set the label to type container_userns_t when you run your container i.e `--security-opt label=type:container_userns_t`. This will ensure it gets the masking policy.
When you build using buildah inside this container please set the --isolation flag to chroot as well i.e `--isolation chroot`.
Let me know if these suggestions help!
